1. Q. What is Div?
Ans.

<div>

- The <div> tag defines a division or a section in an HTML document
            or
  The <div> tag	is known as Division tag.
			
- The <div> element is often used as a container for other HTML elements.
- By default, browsers always place a line break before and after the <div>element.
  However, this can be changed with CSS.




2. Q. 

Top 3 ways to center a DIV with CSS

The div tag in HTML is used to define a section or container. CSS is used to style a perticular division. 
A division can be centered using diffrent methods.

Here are some methods for centering a division using CSS.

1- Classic methods  Ex- classic-method.html
2- Grid methods    Ex- grid-method.html
3- Flex Method     Ex- flex-method.html or div-flexbox2.html







  